item.title: Git
item.description: github repository Create a new repository and link it to the local one We access github with our username and password In our account we create a repository At this time, the page will show us a series of commands that must be executed locally. The actions are: We go to local to the directory where our project is We execute git init # this command initializes our directory as a git project.
